parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also cause a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
electrical functions are inoperable or intermittent
the fuse for the fuel pump blows
the vehicle has poor gas mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall or increase speed unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control. Additionally, it can also cause a fire, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: the wiring is damaged or destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control. It can also cause a fire, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
